1
00:01:36,160 --> 00:01:37,039
You got paid.

2
00:01:42,600 --> 00:01:44,860
What's wrong? The amount doesn't match?

3
00:01:46,680 --> 00:01:47,800
It doesn't match.

4
00:01:49,000 --> 00:01:50,460
There's an extra portion.

5
00:01:50,520 --> 00:01:52,320
Did they give you an extra bonus?

6
00:01:53,080 --> 00:01:54,200
Anyway, this extra portion

7
00:01:54,200 --> 00:01:55,530
is wrapped in red paper.

8
00:01:55,560 --> 00:01:57,600
I don't know if it's a bonus or not.

9
00:01:58,880 --> 00:02:00,340
Let me tell you something.

10
00:02:02,040 --> 00:02:03,360
Mr. Tian is very elusive in the mansion,

11
00:02:03,360 --> 00:02:05,240
isn't he?

12
00:02:06,000 --> 00:02:07,800
I saw him chatting with Master

13
00:02:07,800 --> 00:02:08,720
in our cottage.

14
00:02:08,840 --> 00:02:10,370
They talked for a long time.

15
00:02:10,600 --> 00:02:11,680
When?

16
00:02:11,800 --> 00:02:13,240
Why didn't you tell me?

17
00:02:13,960 --> 00:02:15,360
What did they talk about?

18
00:02:15,800 --> 00:02:18,920
They talked about
those complicated things,

19
00:02:19,040 --> 00:02:21,200
the kind Master always talks about.

20
00:02:21,520 --> 00:02:24,600
They were complicated words.
I didn't understand.

21
00:02:25,720 --> 00:02:27,579
Master won't be exposed, will he?

22
00:02:28,040 --> 00:02:29,840
That's exactly what worries me.

23
00:02:30,200 --> 00:02:31,600
Now when I see Mr. Tian's eyes

24
00:02:31,600 --> 00:02:32,860
with that faint smile,

25
00:02:32,880 --> 00:02:34,120
I panic inside.

26
00:02:34,440 --> 00:02:36,360
Do you think Mr. Tian

27
00:02:37,000 --> 00:02:38,640
has discovered us?

28
00:02:38,960 --> 00:02:42,000
But he didn't do anything to us.

29
00:02:42,320 --> 00:02:43,880
He even gave us extra money.

30
00:02:45,200 --> 00:02:47,840
Mr. Tian took us in,

31
00:02:48,320 --> 00:02:49,680
and we deceived him. This isn't right...

32
00:02:49,680 --> 00:02:51,400
Alright, alright. Stop.

33
00:02:51,640 --> 00:02:53,079
Don't look for trouble.

34
00:02:53,200 --> 00:02:54,400
We don't know if

35
00:02:54,440 --> 00:02:55,720
we're overthinking.

36
00:02:56,400 --> 00:02:58,920
Maybe the accountant made a mistake.

37
00:03:02,040 --> 00:03:03,900
If he made a mistake, I'll keep it.

38
00:03:03,920 --> 00:03:04,960
In my life,

39
00:03:05,000 --> 00:03:07,560
what I love most is counting money.

40
00:03:07,640 --> 00:03:09,440
Counting money makes me happy.

41
00:03:09,600 --> 00:03:11,320
I want to be happy a little longer.

42
00:03:11,320 --> 00:03:12,850
I don't care about the rest.

43
00:03:12,960 --> 00:03:14,800
If he made a mistake with the amount,

44
00:03:14,800 --> 00:03:16,600
didn't you think to ask him?

45
00:03:16,800 --> 00:03:18,000
Why would I ask him?

46
00:03:18,240 --> 00:03:19,880
He gave me extra.

47
00:03:20,120 --> 00:03:21,760
I've already pocketed it.

48
00:03:21,840 --> 00:03:23,120
I'm not giving it back.

49
00:03:27,480 --> 00:03:28,540
What are you doing?

50
00:03:28,800 --> 00:03:29,640
I'm going to ask.

51
00:03:29,640 --> 00:03:32,120
If he really made a mistake,
I have to give it back.

52
00:03:32,120 --> 00:03:34,320
Why? He made the mistake himself.

53
00:03:34,400 --> 00:03:36,000
It's not our problem.

54
00:03:45,400 --> 00:03:46,160
It's gone.

55
00:04:06,520 --> 00:04:09,040
Pocketed it? Bah.

56
00:04:14,840 --> 00:04:15,560
Sibao.

57
00:04:15,800 --> 00:04:16,860
Alright, alright.

58
00:04:16,959 --> 00:04:18,420
Are you giving it a shower?

59
00:04:18,680 --> 00:04:20,000
These plants are very delicate.

60
00:04:20,000 --> 00:04:20,680
Don't overwater.

61
00:04:20,680 --> 00:04:21,339
Butler Zhu.

62
00:04:21,519 --> 00:04:22,250
Understood.

63
00:04:23,160 --> 00:04:24,820
Mrs. Meng. What's the matter?

64
00:04:26,160 --> 00:04:28,360
Wanfu's salary isn't correct.

65
00:04:29,000 --> 00:04:29,720
It's double.

66
00:04:29,720 --> 00:04:32,040
Could the accountant have made a mistake?

67
00:04:32,040 --> 00:04:33,040
No mistake.

68
00:04:33,400 --> 00:04:35,880
You worked too. You deserve a salary.

69
00:04:36,120 --> 00:04:37,120
This isn't right.

70
00:04:37,320 --> 00:04:38,280
We agreed I would work

71
00:04:38,280 --> 00:04:40,920
to cover our room and board.

72
00:04:40,960 --> 00:04:42,620
We can't live and eat for free.

73
00:04:42,760 --> 00:04:45,560
Working and getting paid
is perfectly justified.

74
00:04:45,760 --> 00:04:46,890
Don't think so much.

75
00:04:47,880 --> 00:04:48,800
Thank you, Butler Zhu.

76
00:04:48,800 --> 00:04:50,920
But I feel guilty taking this money.

77
00:04:52,680 --> 00:04:54,840
If you really feel that way,

78
00:04:54,880 --> 00:04:56,920
there's a job I can give you.

79
00:04:57,840 --> 00:04:59,800
When Master rests at noon,

80
00:05:00,080 --> 00:05:01,880
he likes someone to read to him.

81
00:05:02,160 --> 00:05:03,840
The person who used to read to Master

82
00:05:03,840 --> 00:05:05,680
left Shanghai because of the war.

83
00:05:05,680 --> 00:05:07,720
Mrs. Meng, would you be willing
to read to Master

84
00:05:07,720 --> 00:05:08,920
for just an hour or two

85
00:05:09,120 --> 00:05:10,480
every noon?

86
00:05:11,320 --> 00:05:12,320
Me read?

87
00:05:14,200 --> 00:05:16,280
I've never done this kind of work.

88
00:05:16,360 --> 00:05:17,690
I might not be suitable.

89
00:05:17,760 --> 00:05:20,020
I'd rather keep working with Miss Sibao.

90
00:05:20,680 --> 00:05:22,080
I think you're suitable.

91
00:05:22,720 --> 00:05:23,200
Mr. Tian.

92
00:05:23,200 --> 00:05:23,840
Mr. Tian.

93
00:05:24,760 --> 00:05:25,490
To be honest,

94
00:05:25,600 --> 00:05:28,240
your work isn't as good as Sibao's.

95
00:05:30,320 --> 00:05:32,180
I think you're better at reading.

96
00:05:32,440 --> 00:05:33,560
You read "The Little Match Girl"

97
00:05:33,560 --> 00:05:35,320
to Yueming.

98
00:05:41,200 --> 00:05:44,040
Of course. If you don't want to,

99
00:05:44,400 --> 00:05:45,659
don't force yourself.

100
00:05:46,280 --> 00:05:47,720
You can do nothing.

101
00:05:48,640 --> 00:05:50,480
But accept this salary.

102
00:05:51,200 --> 00:05:54,080
I never take back money I've paid.

103
00:06:06,360 --> 00:06:08,820
Good thing Mr. Tian
didn't accept the money.

104
00:06:08,880 --> 00:06:10,340
We didn't lose out either.

105
00:06:10,920 --> 00:06:12,320
Not to criticize, Madam,

106
00:06:12,480 --> 00:06:14,280
but you're too honest.

107
00:06:14,680 --> 00:06:16,920
But I can't get paid for doing nothing.

108
00:06:17,520 --> 00:06:19,160
Besides, if Master finds out about this,

109
00:06:19,160 --> 00:06:20,920
he'll definitely say something.

110
00:06:20,920 --> 00:06:22,760
If you don't go and he finds out,

111
00:06:22,840 --> 00:06:24,360
what do you think he'll say about you?

112
00:06:24,360 --> 00:06:25,290
No need to guess.

113
00:06:25,640 --> 00:06:27,840
You and Master are the same.

114
00:06:27,960 --> 00:06:29,640
It's called...

115
00:06:30,120 --> 00:06:31,520
unity of knowledge and action.

116
00:06:31,520 --> 00:06:33,580
You used that expression correctly.

117
00:06:33,720 --> 00:06:36,450
Unity of knowledge and action
is a person's duty.

118
00:06:38,000 --> 00:06:40,280
Mr. Tian said a paid salary

119
00:06:40,320 --> 00:06:42,120
shouldn't be returned.

120
00:06:42,680 --> 00:06:44,920
He asked me to read to him
to earn the salary.

121
00:06:44,920 --> 00:06:45,760
What?

122
00:06:45,960 --> 00:06:46,880
Read books?

123
00:06:48,520 --> 00:06:49,800
Doesn't he know how to read?

124
00:06:49,800 --> 00:06:50,640
He can read.

125
00:06:51,159 --> 00:06:53,400
But he's used to someone reading to him

126
00:06:53,440 --> 00:06:54,800
before his nap.

127
00:06:54,880 --> 00:06:56,760
What a strange habit!

128
00:06:57,159 --> 00:06:57,680
So,

129
00:06:58,280 --> 00:06:59,560
you accepted?

130
00:07:02,240 --> 00:07:03,360
I want to go.

131
00:07:03,920 --> 00:07:05,520
Reading to Mr. Tian

132
00:07:05,560 --> 00:07:07,320
lets me earn more money.

133
00:07:07,680 --> 00:07:08,600
It's not right

134
00:07:08,680 --> 00:07:10,560
for you to support the three of us.

135
00:07:17,160 --> 00:07:18,040
Besides, don't you still want

136
00:07:18,040 --> 00:07:20,560
to go to Wuhan to find Xiaoyue?

137
00:07:21,360 --> 00:07:23,600
We still need to save money.

138
00:07:25,920 --> 00:07:27,120
But I'm telling you,

139
00:07:27,240 --> 00:07:29,280
Mr. Tian is a mystery.

140
00:07:29,320 --> 00:07:30,760
You never know what he's up to.

141
00:07:30,760 --> 00:07:32,020
You need to be careful.

142
00:07:32,120 --> 00:07:34,250
And you must discuss this with Master.

143
00:07:34,600 --> 00:07:37,000
I don't think Master will let you go.

144
00:07:37,640 --> 00:07:39,520
Of course I'll tell Master. And I'm sure

145
00:07:39,520 --> 00:07:41,560
he'll agree.

146
00:07:41,840 --> 00:07:43,280
Master said it himself.

147
00:07:43,520 --> 00:07:45,320
Though Mr. Tian has

148
00:07:45,320 --> 00:07:46,560
Western knowledge,

149
00:07:46,640 --> 00:07:47,560
he understands respect

150
00:07:47,560 --> 00:07:49,420
in Cheng-Zhu Neo-Confucianism.

151
00:07:49,760 --> 00:07:51,820
Master trusts Mr. Tian's character.

152
00:07:52,600 --> 00:07:53,680
You intellectuals always speak

153
00:07:53,680 --> 00:07:55,880
in winding and twisting ways.

154
00:07:56,320 --> 00:07:58,320
What's this about respecting pigs?

155
00:07:58,360 --> 00:07:59,280
You respect pigs?

156
00:07:59,280 --> 00:08:01,080
Cheng-Zhu Neo-Confucianism.

157
00:08:01,720 --> 00:08:03,840
Are you coming or not?
There are so many cars outside.

158
00:08:03,840 --> 00:08:04,400
Who knows how far

159
00:08:04,400 --> 00:08:06,060
Master and Yueming have gone.

160
00:08:06,560 --> 00:08:07,880
Let's go.

161
00:08:09,960 --> 00:08:11,200
Wait for me.

162
00:08:14,560 --> 00:08:15,560
Wait for me!

163
00:08:33,159 --> 00:08:34,080
Mr. Tian.

164
00:08:35,840 --> 00:08:36,760
Come in.

165
00:08:49,120 --> 00:08:50,240
What should I read?

166
00:08:51,960 --> 00:08:53,020
Whatever you like.

167
00:08:53,200 --> 00:08:54,460
The books are all here.

168
00:08:55,200 --> 00:08:56,530
Read anything you want.

169
00:09:34,800 --> 00:09:36,280
Can I read "Don Quixote?"

170
00:09:36,760 --> 00:09:37,400
Sure.

171
00:09:52,480 --> 00:09:53,320
Thank you.

172
00:10:17,360 --> 00:10:19,760
Then I'll start from the bookmark.

173
00:10:20,440 --> 00:10:21,080
Okay.

174
00:10:24,040 --> 00:10:27,240
The innkeeper saw his guest
kneeling at his feet.

175
00:10:27,760 --> 00:10:29,600
Hearing such words,

176
00:10:29,920 --> 00:10:31,600
he stared, astonished,

177
00:10:32,280 --> 00:10:35,680
not knowing what to say or do.

178
00:10:36,160 --> 00:10:38,720
He struggled to help him up

179
00:10:38,720 --> 00:10:39,720
and granted his request.

180
00:10:39,720 --> 00:10:40,600
Compared to

181
00:10:41,480 --> 00:10:43,880
the first time I heard your voice,

182
00:10:44,880 --> 00:10:46,800
you don't seem very relaxed.

183
00:10:47,560 --> 00:10:50,200
Is it because I'm here?
Are you not used to it?

184
00:10:52,880 --> 00:10:55,000
Sorry. I'll try again.

185
00:10:58,960 --> 00:11:00,840
But it was all for nothing.

186
00:11:01,440 --> 00:11:03,680
He agreed to the requested favor.

187
00:11:04,000 --> 00:11:07,720
Don Quixote stood up and said:

188
00:11:08,080 --> 00:11:11,440
That's exactly what I hoped for.

189
00:11:11,800 --> 00:11:12,760
Let's do this.

190
00:11:15,440 --> 00:11:17,120
Let's find a way

191
00:11:17,600 --> 00:11:19,640
to help each other relax.

192
00:11:27,760 --> 00:11:28,760
Keep reading.

193
00:11:51,520 --> 00:11:53,680
Then I'll tell you.

194
00:11:54,600 --> 00:11:57,520
What I requested and...

195
00:12:05,040 --> 00:12:06,040
What I requested,

196
00:12:06,040 --> 00:12:08,640
and you generously accepted, is

197
00:12:08,840 --> 00:12:11,560
for you to knight me tomorrow.

198
00:12:11,680 --> 00:12:14,080
Tonight, I'll watch over my arms

199
00:12:14,120 --> 00:12:17,080
in your fortress's chapel.

200
00:12:18,200 --> 00:12:19,320
Tomorrow,

201
00:12:20,440 --> 00:12:22,080
as I've said,

202
00:12:22,680 --> 00:12:26,200
my deepest desire will be fulfilled.

203
00:12:26,400 --> 00:12:29,480
Then I can officially travel the world.

204
00:12:34,400 --> 00:12:35,400
Mr. Tian,

205
00:12:36,200 --> 00:12:38,200
can you hear me when I read like this?

206
00:12:39,800 --> 00:12:40,840
Mr. Tian.

207
00:13:00,760 --> 00:13:01,720
I clearly heard...

208
00:13:01,720 --> 00:13:03,050
I heard it very clearly.

209
00:13:05,320 --> 00:13:06,880
If you want and feel comfortable,

210
00:13:06,880 --> 00:13:08,080
you can read

211
00:13:08,400 --> 00:13:09,520
here.

212
00:13:19,000 --> 00:13:20,320
This is a place

213
00:13:21,800 --> 00:13:23,680
where I can really relax.

214
00:13:26,680 --> 00:13:27,720
It's true.

215
00:13:30,840 --> 00:13:32,680
Modified Stearman 6-P.

216
00:13:33,200 --> 00:13:34,680
In the 24th year of the Republic of China,

217
00:13:34,680 --> 00:13:37,280
I flew it in the Alps.

218
00:13:39,320 --> 00:13:41,120
Later, the plane crashed.

219
00:13:41,160 --> 00:13:43,520
The wreckage was abandoned there.

220
00:13:43,720 --> 00:13:45,800
So I brought this cockpit over.

221
00:13:46,640 --> 00:13:50,440
Now it's just for decoration.

222
00:13:51,360 --> 00:13:53,120
It can't leave this room.

223
00:13:54,880 --> 00:13:55,680
Have a seat.

224
00:14:14,040 --> 00:14:15,240
You can keep reading.

225
00:14:38,040 --> 00:14:39,600
I'll do dangerous things

226
00:14:39,880 --> 00:14:41,210
and rescue those in need

227
00:14:41,680 --> 00:14:44,480
to fulfill the duties
of knights and adventurers.

228
00:14:44,760 --> 00:14:46,720
These people are like me.

229
00:14:46,800 --> 00:14:49,730
They're wholeheartedly dedicated
to these causes.

230
00:14:49,880 --> 00:14:52,560
The innkeeper, as we said,

231
00:14:52,800 --> 00:14:54,440
was a cunning fellow.

232
00:14:54,680 --> 00:14:56,480
He already had his suspicions,

233
00:14:56,840 --> 00:14:59,600
He imagined his guest was mad.

234
00:14:59,800 --> 00:15:02,930
Now, hearing these words,
he was completely convinced.

235
00:15:03,120 --> 00:15:06,400
He wanted to have some fun that night.

236
00:15:06,560 --> 00:15:09,440
So he decided to play along.

237
00:15:09,520 --> 00:15:12,040
So he said to him:

238
00:15:12,280 --> 00:15:15,480
"What you ask is right.

239
00:15:15,840 --> 00:15:18,960
Your appearance and noble bearing prove

240
00:15:18,960 --> 00:15:23,520
you are a distinguished knight."

241
00:15:23,880 --> 00:15:28,720
Doing this kind of cause was inevitable.

242
00:15:43,960 --> 00:15:44,800
Excuse me.

243
00:15:46,520 --> 00:15:47,400
Keep reading.

244
00:15:53,200 --> 00:15:54,400
He's a madman.

245
00:15:55,640 --> 00:15:56,560
And a fool.

246
00:15:57,920 --> 00:15:59,680
Do you think he's a madman?

247
00:16:04,840 --> 00:16:06,400
Yes, he's a bit crazy.

248
00:16:06,600 --> 00:16:07,880
But in my opinion,

249
00:16:08,400 --> 00:16:10,200
he's a very fascinating madman.

250
00:16:10,400 --> 00:16:11,800
What chivalrous spirit?

251
00:16:12,160 --> 00:16:13,800
He's simply crazy and foolish.

252
00:16:13,800 --> 00:16:16,560
And thinks he can fascinate the world.

253
00:16:19,000 --> 00:16:20,460
Please continue reading.

254
00:16:30,000 --> 00:16:30,760
Chef Meng.

255
00:16:55,560 --> 00:16:56,160
Douzi,

256
00:16:56,200 --> 00:16:57,440
is Mr. Tian's soup ready?

257
00:16:57,440 --> 00:16:58,400
Coming.

258
00:17:00,560 --> 00:17:00,960
It's hot!

259
00:17:00,960 --> 00:17:01,440
Ready!

260
00:17:08,599 --> 00:17:10,160
Sibao, this is Mr. Tian's afternoon tea,

261
00:17:10,160 --> 00:17:11,640
right?

262
00:17:12,000 --> 00:17:12,640
Yes.

263
00:17:12,960 --> 00:17:14,800
How about I take it?

264
00:17:14,920 --> 00:17:15,960
You? You take it?

265
00:17:16,680 --> 00:17:17,839
I'll inform him of next week's menu

266
00:17:17,839 --> 00:17:19,000
while I'm at it.

267
00:17:19,920 --> 00:17:21,079
Help me beat the eggs.

268
00:17:21,079 --> 00:17:21,920
Sure. No problem.

269
00:17:21,920 --> 00:17:22,640
Be right back.

270
00:17:22,640 --> 00:17:23,300
No problem.

271
00:17:25,960 --> 00:17:27,920
Thus the valiant Don Quixote

272
00:17:28,000 --> 00:17:29,720
defended justice.

273
00:17:30,000 --> 00:17:32,520
He thought that as soon as he began,
he accomplished the most successful
and glorious knightly enterprise.

274
00:17:32,520 --> 00:17:35,400
He felt

275
00:17:35,600 --> 00:17:38,040
infinite joy.

276
00:17:38,400 --> 00:17:39,480
Satisfied,

277
00:17:39,520 --> 00:17:41,640
as he advanced toward his estate,

278
00:17:41,800 --> 00:17:43,280
he said in a low voice,

279
00:17:43,960 --> 00:17:46,040
"Oh, Dulcinea del Toboso."

280
00:17:46,200 --> 00:17:48,560
A beauty among beauties.

281
00:17:48,800 --> 00:17:51,160
You can consider yourself

282
00:17:53,720 --> 00:17:56,840
the most fortunate woman in the world.

283
00:17:57,120 --> 00:17:57,560
Master...

284
00:17:57,560 --> 00:17:58,220
Because...

285
00:17:58,440 --> 00:17:59,240
Afternoon tea.

286
00:17:59,240 --> 00:18:01,640
You are destined to have a knight

287
00:18:01,720 --> 00:18:04,880
like Don Quixote,

288
00:18:05,720 --> 00:18:09,760
brave and famous,

289
00:18:09,880 --> 00:18:15,920
who obeys your will
and follows your heart.

290
00:18:17,400 --> 00:18:21,680
The whole world already knows this knight.

291
00:18:22,040 --> 00:18:24,640
He was knighted only yesterday.

292
00:18:24,760 --> 00:18:29,520
Today he eliminated
the evil born of injustice,

293
00:18:29,640 --> 00:18:31,640
the greatest harm

294
00:18:33,840 --> 00:18:35,200
and misfortune.

295
00:18:38,320 --> 00:18:41,960
He snatched the whip

296
00:18:42,320 --> 00:18:43,480
from the wicked enemy

297
00:18:43,480 --> 00:18:45,880
beating a defenseless child for no reason.

298
00:18:46,400 --> 00:18:50,280
Upon arriving at
the crossroads of four paths,

299
00:18:50,360 --> 00:18:52,440
he immediately remembered when...

300
00:19:09,960 --> 00:19:13,880
Upon arriving at
the crossroads of four paths,

301
00:19:14,240 --> 00:19:16,960
He immediately remembered

302
00:19:17,600 --> 00:19:20,600
when wandering knights
encounter these crossroads,

303
00:19:20,600 --> 00:19:22,640
they always stop to think

304
00:19:22,760 --> 00:19:24,160
about which path to take.

305
00:19:41,000 --> 00:19:41,880
Chef Jiao,

306
00:19:42,240 --> 00:19:44,360
maybe our cooking habits are different,

307
00:19:44,360 --> 00:19:45,880
but I think it's better to cut

308
00:19:45,880 --> 00:19:47,320
these chiles into diagonal strips.

309
00:19:47,320 --> 00:19:50,040
They look better
when stir-fried this way. Thank you.

310
00:19:50,040 --> 00:19:52,600
Alright. You're the head chef.

311
00:19:53,000 --> 00:19:54,120
You decide.

312
00:19:58,600 --> 00:19:59,280
Chef Meng,

313
00:19:59,960 --> 00:20:01,000
prepare two afternoon teas.

314
00:20:01,000 --> 00:20:02,520
Take them to the study soon.

315
00:20:02,520 --> 00:20:03,720
Two portions, right?

316
00:20:03,800 --> 00:20:04,520
Alright.

317
00:20:08,240 --> 00:20:08,880
Wanfu.

318
00:20:11,040 --> 00:20:13,720
What book does your wife read to Mr. Tian?

319
00:20:13,880 --> 00:20:15,280
He really likes it.

320
00:20:15,480 --> 00:20:18,010
If there's a chance,
have her read it to me too.

321
00:20:19,640 --> 00:20:21,880
What are you insinuating
with that sarcastic tone?

322
00:20:21,880 --> 00:20:23,340
She's not taking your job.

323
00:20:24,040 --> 00:20:25,880
Who cares about my job?

324
00:20:26,160 --> 00:20:28,120
Some people get this position
and think they're so capable,

325
00:20:28,120 --> 00:20:29,680
but in the end they still have to rely

326
00:20:29,680 --> 00:20:31,400
on their wife.

327
00:20:31,800 --> 00:20:32,920
Say that again!

328
00:20:33,000 --> 00:20:34,400
Did I say something wrong?

329
00:20:34,400 --> 00:20:35,640
What's going on here?

330
00:20:38,560 --> 00:20:40,090
Are there no rules anymore?

331
00:20:43,800 --> 00:20:44,560
Jiao,

332
00:20:45,320 --> 00:20:47,440
what the master does and how he does it,

333
00:20:47,440 --> 00:20:49,440
is it your place to gossip?

334
00:20:50,240 --> 00:20:51,880
If I hear this again,

335
00:20:52,120 --> 00:20:54,120
don't blame me for being rude to you!

336
00:20:54,800 --> 00:20:55,560
Understood.

337
00:21:02,400 --> 00:21:03,660
Wanfu, that's enough.

338
00:21:03,840 --> 00:21:06,800
Mrs. Meng is just reading to the master.

339
00:21:06,840 --> 00:21:07,640
It's nothing.

340
00:21:10,000 --> 00:21:10,840
Douzi,

341
00:21:11,600 --> 00:21:13,280
have you finished moving
the red wine and milk

342
00:21:13,280 --> 00:21:14,120
that arrived?

343
00:21:14,440 --> 00:21:15,370
A few boxes left.

344
00:21:15,400 --> 00:21:16,560
Hurry up.

345
00:21:30,400 --> 00:21:31,000
Chef Meng.

346
00:21:32,800 --> 00:21:33,640
Wanfu.

347
00:21:47,400 --> 00:21:50,000
This Mr. Tian is really studious.

348
00:21:50,440 --> 00:21:52,200
How did the master say it?

349
00:21:53,040 --> 00:21:55,120
The big mattress can still cry out.

350
00:21:55,560 --> 00:21:57,360
The mattress really can cry out.

351
00:21:58,760 --> 00:22:00,480
Reading at noon was fine,

352
00:22:00,760 --> 00:22:03,200
but now you read
in the morning and afternoon too.

353
00:22:03,200 --> 00:22:04,680
What kind of special book are you reading

354
00:22:04,680 --> 00:22:05,880
that's so addictive?

355
00:22:06,440 --> 00:22:09,170
Who offended you?
Why are you talking so harshly?

356
00:22:10,920 --> 00:22:12,760
Now the gossip has started.

357
00:22:13,200 --> 00:22:14,800
You don't know
how Chef Jiao and his people

358
00:22:14,800 --> 00:22:16,520
whisper in private

359
00:22:16,600 --> 00:22:18,060
and say such nasty things.

360
00:22:18,920 --> 00:22:21,080
Well, I work and earn money honestly.

361
00:22:21,160 --> 00:22:22,620
I don't care what they say.

362
00:22:37,360 --> 00:22:38,890
This month's salary, here.

363
00:22:39,560 --> 00:22:41,320
Keep the money you earned.

364
00:22:41,440 --> 00:22:42,480
Why are you giving it to me?

365
00:22:42,480 --> 00:22:44,240
Didn't you buy medicine for Father?

366
00:22:44,240 --> 00:22:45,770
I have to give you the money.

367
00:22:46,720 --> 00:22:48,640
What's this about yours and mine?

368
00:22:49,160 --> 00:22:50,960
Are you keeping score with me?

369
00:22:53,960 --> 00:22:56,760
Yueming needs some new toys,

370
00:22:56,840 --> 00:22:59,960
and the master needs some new clothes too.

371
00:23:00,720 --> 00:23:03,450
Don't you want to get
something for yourself too?

372
00:23:05,560 --> 00:23:07,760
I don't need anything. I have clothes.

373
00:23:10,360 --> 00:23:13,520
Well then,
if we have time off on Saturday,

374
00:23:13,920 --> 00:23:15,180
let's go out together.

375
00:23:20,160 --> 00:23:21,620
Yueming hasn't eaten yet.

376
00:23:31,160 --> 00:23:32,240
Your food is on the table.

377
00:23:32,240 --> 00:23:33,840
Eat yours first.

378
00:23:34,080 --> 00:23:35,120
Alright.

379
00:23:48,680 --> 00:23:51,440
Victory in southern Henan
and eastern Hubei.

380
00:23:51,640 --> 00:23:55,240
The Japanese troops are cornered.

381
00:23:55,600 --> 00:23:59,040
Our reinforcements counterattacked
with great success.

382
00:24:00,000 --> 00:24:03,560
Since the battles in southern Henan and eastern Hubei began
in our strategic territory,

383
00:24:03,560 --> 00:24:07,280
we've repeatedly defeated

384
00:24:08,200 --> 00:24:10,440
the Japanese

385
00:24:10,560 --> 00:24:12,490
and won extraordinary victories.

386
00:24:13,360 --> 00:24:16,160
Victory on the southern bank
of the Yangtze River.

387
00:24:16,400 --> 00:24:20,080
Qilin Peak on the Ruiwu line
has been liberated.

388
00:24:20,840 --> 00:24:22,760
In the Battle of Qilin Peak,

389
00:24:23,120 --> 00:24:25,720
on the night of the 26th,

390
00:24:26,080 --> 00:24:30,360
we annihilated the Japanese 2nd Regiment
on Baishui Street.

391
00:24:31,440 --> 00:24:33,080
Victory in northern Henan.

392
00:24:33,520 --> 00:24:36,040
We recovered Wuzhi in Meng County.

393
00:24:36,480 --> 00:24:39,200
We killed an enemy brigade commander.

394
00:24:41,160 --> 00:24:42,000
Besides your leg,

395
00:24:42,000 --> 00:24:44,040
do you feel discomfort anywhere else?

396
00:24:44,040 --> 00:24:46,000
Besides my leg, everything else is fine.

397
00:24:46,000 --> 00:24:47,200
Good. That's fine then.

398
00:24:47,200 --> 00:24:49,260
I'll treat it in a bit. You'll be fine.

399
00:24:53,880 --> 00:24:54,920
Slowly. No rush.

400
00:25:00,840 --> 00:25:01,960
These damn Japs.

401
00:25:02,760 --> 00:25:04,820
Why fire on the Mid-Autumn Festival?

402
00:25:04,920 --> 00:25:07,000
Couldn't they let us celebrate in peace

403
00:25:07,000 --> 00:25:08,130
and fight tomorrow?

404
00:25:08,480 --> 00:25:10,480
Don't they celebrate the festival?

405
00:25:11,640 --> 00:25:12,370
Yes, they do.

406
00:25:12,760 --> 00:25:14,200
It's from the Tang Dynasty.

407
00:25:14,200 --> 00:25:16,730
In Japan, some call it
"The Fifteenth Night."

408
00:25:17,280 --> 00:25:20,320
So these bastards also celebrate
the Mid-Autumn Festival.

409
00:25:20,320 --> 00:25:21,960
So why fire, knowing it's a festival?

410
00:25:21,960 --> 00:25:23,890
They don't deserve this festival.

411
00:25:24,280 --> 00:25:25,410
Never mind all that.

412
00:25:25,600 --> 00:25:27,440
The food is good today.

413
00:25:27,560 --> 00:25:28,880
Let's eat well first.

414
00:25:29,160 --> 00:25:32,320
When we're full,
we'll give them a good fight.

415
00:25:32,520 --> 00:25:33,440
Happy Mid-Autumn.

416
00:25:33,440 --> 00:25:34,370
Happy festival.

417
00:25:35,440 --> 00:25:36,520
Nice flower.

418
00:25:36,560 --> 00:25:37,440
Happy Mid-Autumn.

419
00:25:37,440 --> 00:25:38,520
You too.

420
00:25:40,920 --> 00:25:41,980
Happy Mid-Autumn.

421
00:25:42,480 --> 00:25:46,120
I just heard someone say we're retreating.

422
00:25:46,240 --> 00:25:47,500
So, are we retreating?

423
00:25:47,560 --> 00:25:49,040
Tell the buddies to pack up.

424
00:25:49,040 --> 00:25:50,880
Be ready to retreat at any time.

425
00:25:51,560 --> 00:25:53,720
Didn't they say we could defend Wuhan?

426
00:25:54,120 --> 00:25:56,040
The Japanese Army's battle lines

427
00:25:56,160 --> 00:25:58,560
are being stretched thin.

428
00:25:58,640 --> 00:26:01,000
Battlefields have opened
behind enemy lines.

429
00:26:01,000 --> 00:26:02,480
They resist continuously.

430
00:26:02,480 --> 00:26:04,000
They retreat to the mountains.

431
00:26:04,000 --> 00:26:06,600
The Japanese heavy weapons
are useless there.

432
00:26:07,520 --> 00:26:08,840
Last year at Pingxingguan,

433
00:26:08,840 --> 00:26:11,570
that battle shattered
the Japanese Army's myth.

434
00:26:11,720 --> 00:26:13,760
The weak can defeat the strong.

435
00:26:13,880 --> 00:26:15,440
Look at Jiangnan's New Fourth Army.

436
00:26:15,440 --> 00:26:16,770
Their ambush at Weigang

437
00:26:17,040 --> 00:26:18,560
was very strategic.

438
00:26:19,040 --> 00:26:20,400
But even so,

439
00:26:20,920 --> 00:26:23,120
I'm still a bit worried about the south.

440
00:26:24,880 --> 00:26:26,160
The south?

441
00:26:26,840 --> 00:26:28,080
Which south?

442
00:26:28,280 --> 00:26:30,400
We've been withdrawing troops
to protect Wuhan.

443
00:26:30,400 --> 00:26:34,120
I'm worried the Japanese will use this chance
to attack Guangzhou.

444
00:26:34,120 --> 00:26:35,240
Guangzhou?

445
00:26:35,560 --> 00:26:37,560
Impossible. Guangzhou is too far away.

446
00:26:37,560 --> 00:26:38,360
Yes. It's far.

447
00:26:39,760 --> 00:26:41,600
But if Guangzhou falls,

448
00:26:41,960 --> 00:26:43,960
the sea transport lines will be cut off.

449
00:26:43,960 --> 00:26:46,080
Japanese will push north
up the Guangzhou-Wuhan line.

450
00:26:46,080 --> 00:26:48,240
Then Wuhan would become

451
00:26:48,280 --> 00:26:49,560
an isolated city.

452
00:26:49,680 --> 00:26:52,520
At that point, the Generalissimo
might lose confidence

453
00:26:52,520 --> 00:26:54,760
and abandon Wuhan.

454
00:26:55,120 --> 00:26:57,000
If Wuhan is abandoned,

455
00:26:57,240 --> 00:26:58,520
what will we do?

456
00:26:59,040 --> 00:26:59,900
If Wuhan falls,

457
00:26:59,960 --> 00:27:01,920
most of Central China and South China

458
00:27:01,920 --> 00:27:03,160
will be occupied by the Japanese Army.

459
00:27:03,160 --> 00:27:05,400
But with their current strength,
it'll be hard for the Japanese Army

460
00:27:05,400 --> 00:27:07,160
to control that many regions.

461
00:27:07,600 --> 00:27:09,640
This gives us a lot of space

462
00:27:09,960 --> 00:27:12,120
for guerrilla warfare behind enemy lines.

463
00:27:12,120 --> 00:27:12,800
I didn't understand what you

464
00:27:12,800 --> 00:27:14,360
just said.

465
00:27:14,640 --> 00:27:15,900
Explain it to me again.

466
00:27:16,280 --> 00:27:19,480
I mean I want to stay
and start a guerrilla war.

467
00:27:20,680 --> 00:27:22,440
Guerrilla warfare requires no identity.

468
00:27:22,440 --> 00:27:24,480
I can hide myself, preserve my strength,

469
00:27:24,480 --> 00:27:26,120
and act according to circumstances.

470
00:27:26,120 --> 00:27:28,380
When the time is right, I'll strike them.

471
00:27:28,520 --> 00:27:31,450
Anyway, fighting the Japanese
is the same anywhere.

472
00:27:32,040 --> 00:27:32,760
You,

473
00:27:33,560 --> 00:27:34,400
you're different from me.

474
00:27:34,400 --> 00:27:36,260
Take the men and find the old unit.

475
00:27:36,520 --> 00:27:38,240
No need to get implicated by me.

476
00:27:38,240 --> 00:27:39,600
What do you mean by that?

477
00:27:40,440 --> 00:27:42,200
Didn't I make my position clear?

478
00:27:42,200 --> 00:27:44,560
I'll go wherever you go.

479
00:27:45,320 --> 00:27:47,780
You said you wanted
to be a guerrilla, right?

480
00:27:47,800 --> 00:27:50,240
With one order from you,
I'll recruit men immediately.

481
00:27:50,240 --> 00:27:51,440
You'll be the commander,

482
00:27:51,440 --> 00:27:53,300
and I'll be the deputy commander.

483
00:27:53,880 --> 00:27:55,520
Happy Mid-Autumn Festival.

484
00:27:55,800 --> 00:27:56,800
Have a mooncake.

485
00:27:57,560 --> 00:27:58,040
Here.

486
00:27:58,080 --> 00:27:58,760
Xiaoyue.

487
00:27:59,800 --> 00:28:00,160
Thanks.

488
00:28:00,160 --> 00:28:01,120
Great!

489
00:28:03,080 --> 00:28:05,040
Your leg healed? Are you okay now?

490
00:28:05,280 --> 00:28:06,800
Of course my leg isn't okay.

491
00:28:06,800 --> 00:28:08,040
But I got excited

492
00:28:08,280 --> 00:28:10,040
when I saw you coming.

493
00:28:17,520 --> 00:28:18,360
Miss Xiaoyue,

494
00:28:18,600 --> 00:28:20,600
what's the filling of this mooncake?

495
00:28:20,600 --> 00:28:21,680
Foxtail grass.

496
00:28:21,960 --> 00:28:23,400
You're so funny.

497
00:28:23,800 --> 00:28:26,000
There's no mooncake with that filling.

498
00:28:27,680 --> 00:28:29,960
Miss Xiaoyue, for heroes like us

499
00:28:29,960 --> 00:28:32,120
who risk our lives,

500
00:28:32,240 --> 00:28:33,900
you only give us one mooncake?

501
00:28:34,600 --> 00:28:37,160
Okay, I'll give you two more.

502
00:28:38,440 --> 00:28:39,480
Catch them.

503
00:28:43,840 --> 00:28:44,440
Here.

504
00:28:46,400 --> 00:28:46,960
Good.

505
00:28:47,200 --> 00:28:49,040
Save me some good dishes.

506
00:28:49,280 --> 00:28:50,740
Go eat your foxtail grass.

507
00:28:51,320 --> 00:28:53,080
Come. Have some mooncakes.

508
00:28:53,400 --> 00:28:54,400
You, your illness

509
00:28:54,880 --> 00:28:56,160
serves you well.

510
00:28:57,080 --> 00:28:58,340
Depends on the person.

511
00:28:58,400 --> 00:28:59,680
Happy Mid-Autumn Festival.

512
00:28:59,680 --> 00:29:02,280
Come get mooncakes.
Happy Mid-Autumn Festival.

513
00:29:02,280 --> 00:29:03,880
Have a mooncake.

514
00:29:08,440 --> 00:29:11,880
It hurts even to laugh.

515
00:29:23,840 --> 00:29:27,840
I say that the words
before the Northern Song Dynasty are also like this.

516
00:29:27,920 --> 00:29:30,760
However, what Canglang called "interest"

517
00:29:30,960 --> 00:29:33,220
and what Ruanting called "divine charm"

518
00:29:33,360 --> 00:29:35,280
only describe their appearance.

519
00:29:35,680 --> 00:29:38,320
Not like my concept of "realm,"
which explores

520
00:29:38,480 --> 00:29:40,480
its essence.

521
00:29:57,120 --> 00:29:58,320
Five minutes left.

522
00:29:58,520 --> 00:29:59,840
Weren't you asleep?

523
00:30:01,000 --> 00:30:02,060
I wasn't sleeping.

524
00:30:03,480 --> 00:30:05,200
I just heard you snoring.

525
00:30:06,920 --> 00:30:08,560
I just relaxed a bit.

526
00:30:09,200 --> 00:30:11,730
I never snore.
I was listening the whole time.

527
00:30:15,400 --> 00:30:18,280
This Mr. Jing'an is very arrogant.

528
00:30:18,560 --> 00:30:20,440
It turns out that
since the Northern Song Dynasty,

529
00:30:20,440 --> 00:30:22,240
all theories of poetry and verse

530
00:30:22,600 --> 00:30:24,800
don't compare to his theory of "realm."

531
00:30:25,560 --> 00:30:27,640
And you say Mr. Wang Guowei is arrogant?

532
00:30:27,640 --> 00:30:28,840
But he's not a blatant liar

533
00:30:28,840 --> 00:30:30,280
like you.

534
00:30:32,360 --> 00:30:33,600
But having said that,

535
00:30:34,400 --> 00:30:37,200
Wang Guowei wasn't all talk and no action.

536
00:30:37,560 --> 00:30:40,200
After all, he put the ideal he pursued

537
00:30:40,560 --> 00:30:42,440
into his own works,

538
00:30:43,320 --> 00:30:44,600
like in "Cai Sang Zi."

539
00:30:45,360 --> 00:30:47,800
Life is like fluff before the wind.

540
00:30:48,280 --> 00:30:50,920
Joy is scarce. Sorrow is scarce.

541
00:30:51,480 --> 00:30:53,880
All become duckweed floating on the river.

542
00:30:55,040 --> 00:30:56,640
Using his theory of spirit,

543
00:30:57,480 --> 00:30:58,640
what do you think?

544
00:30:59,560 --> 00:31:00,760
I can't comment

545
00:31:02,400 --> 00:31:03,360
on this poem.

546
00:31:04,720 --> 00:31:06,650
I can only empathize with the poet.

547
00:31:10,120 --> 00:31:12,320
Is it because of the change in identity?

548
00:31:15,200 --> 00:31:17,360
Do you know that Yueming was born

549
00:31:17,440 --> 00:31:21,480
on December 13, 1937?

550
00:31:24,080 --> 00:31:25,320
The day Nanjing fell.

551
00:31:25,720 --> 00:31:26,760
That day,

552
00:31:27,240 --> 00:31:31,280
Father and I wanted to enter
the concession.

553
00:31:31,680 --> 00:31:34,360
The French blocked us
and wouldn't let us in.

554
00:31:34,760 --> 00:31:37,160
The Japanese were chasing the guerrillas.

555
00:31:37,600 --> 00:31:39,460
There were gunshots everywhere.

556
00:31:39,960 --> 00:31:43,360
Father and I got separated
at the entrance of the concession.

557
00:31:44,480 --> 00:31:46,080
Wanfu took me to hide

558
00:31:46,160 --> 00:31:49,120
in some ruins in the Chinese district.

559
00:31:50,040 --> 00:31:52,320
Japanese soldiers were searching
for guerrillas outside.

560
00:31:52,320 --> 00:31:53,850
We didn't dare make a sound.

561
00:31:55,040 --> 00:31:56,640
They killed anyone they saw.

562
00:31:57,920 --> 00:31:59,840
I remember in those ruins,

563
00:32:00,440 --> 00:32:03,560
a bayonet pried open

564
00:32:03,640 --> 00:32:05,400
the window above our heads.

565
00:32:05,840 --> 00:32:08,160
When the bayonet was closest to me,

566
00:32:08,960 --> 00:32:12,320
it was no more than 5 centimeters
above my head.

567
00:32:13,080 --> 00:32:16,960
It was covered in blood.
It was a very dark color,

568
00:32:18,320 --> 00:32:20,240
as dark as red bean paste.

569
00:32:21,040 --> 00:32:23,560
In a broken mirror in those ruins,

570
00:32:23,880 --> 00:32:25,320
I saw that man's face.

571
00:32:26,120 --> 00:32:27,850
It was the most terrifying face

572
00:32:28,480 --> 00:32:30,040
I've ever seen in my life.

573
00:32:30,960 --> 00:32:34,360
We didn't dare make a sound.

574
00:32:34,520 --> 00:32:38,240
They killed a mother and her four children

575
00:32:38,520 --> 00:32:40,360
right before my eyes.

576
00:32:42,040 --> 00:32:47,000
The youngest child was only 4 years old.

577
00:32:47,240 --> 00:32:50,040
The children came out one by one

578
00:32:50,560 --> 00:32:52,280
and were killed one by one.

579
00:32:52,520 --> 00:32:54,680
Their mother broke down.
She rushed out to save her children.

580
00:32:54,680 --> 00:32:56,960
They killed her

581
00:32:58,080 --> 00:32:59,280
too.

582
00:33:00,320 --> 00:33:02,450
I had never seen anyone killed before.

583
00:33:02,520 --> 00:33:04,160
I used to think gunshots

584
00:33:04,240 --> 00:33:05,880
would be very

585
00:33:06,200 --> 00:33:08,680
piercing and sharp.

586
00:33:09,000 --> 00:33:10,360
But I never imagined

587
00:33:11,880 --> 00:33:14,320
it would be such a dull sound, like...

588
00:33:15,440 --> 00:33:17,200
like frying beans.

589
00:33:17,320 --> 00:33:19,040
Just one pop.

590
00:33:19,400 --> 00:33:20,640
A person was gone.

591
00:33:20,640 --> 00:33:23,040
One pop. A person was gone.

592
00:33:24,000 --> 00:33:25,120
That mother died

593
00:33:25,160 --> 00:33:27,600
less than 20 meters away from me.

594
00:33:28,080 --> 00:33:29,720
When she fell to the ground,

595
00:33:30,080 --> 00:33:32,540
her eyes were still looking
at her children.

596
00:33:34,120 --> 00:33:35,760
Time passed so slowly.

597
00:33:36,840 --> 00:33:38,970
Finally, the Japanese soldiers left.

598
00:33:39,720 --> 00:33:42,520
Yueming was born.

599
00:33:44,000 --> 00:33:47,280
The day Yueming was born, this was

600
00:33:47,960 --> 00:33:50,160
the first thing the world showed him.

601
00:34:08,760 --> 00:34:10,489
When my mother gave birth to me,

602
00:34:10,840 --> 00:34:12,320
Father wasn't happy.

603
00:34:13,280 --> 00:34:15,760
My mother really wanted a daughter.

604
00:34:16,639 --> 00:34:18,520
I already had an older brother.

605
00:34:21,239 --> 00:34:22,880
So when I was born,

606
00:34:23,280 --> 00:34:26,880
the midwife carried me out
of the delivery room.

607
00:34:27,639 --> 00:34:28,969
As soon as Father saw me,

608
00:34:29,719 --> 00:34:31,440
he said to the midwife,

609
00:34:32,320 --> 00:34:34,449
"Take him away. Take him away quickly.

610
00:34:34,960 --> 00:34:36,620
Don't let his mother see him."

611
00:34:37,120 --> 00:34:40,050
Then he entered the delivery room
and told my mother,

612
00:34:40,600 --> 00:34:42,460
"Congratulations, it's a girl."

613
00:34:55,840 --> 00:34:56,760
And then?

614
00:34:57,080 --> 00:34:58,760
Then my mother told my father,

615
00:34:59,080 --> 00:35:00,080
"I'm just in pain.

616
00:35:00,120 --> 00:35:01,040
I'm not blind."

617
00:35:12,560 --> 00:35:15,090
You've been reading to me
for several months,

618
00:35:15,640 --> 00:35:17,770
but I still don't know what to call you.

619
00:35:19,240 --> 00:35:21,720
Mrs. Meng. That's what everyone calls me.

620
00:35:26,880 --> 00:35:27,760
Ding Yujiao.

621
00:35:29,080 --> 00:35:30,000
Ding Yujiao.

622
00:35:31,600 --> 00:35:33,130
Just at the perfect moment.

623
00:35:33,520 --> 00:35:35,840
The moon (Yujiao) becomes full tonight.

624
00:35:36,040 --> 00:35:38,320
It's a very common and beautiful name.

625
00:35:39,040 --> 00:35:39,800
Thank you.

626
00:35:41,280 --> 00:35:42,540
My name is Tian Jiatai.

627
00:35:43,360 --> 00:35:44,160
I go by Hechen.

628
00:35:46,080 --> 00:35:47,880
Nice to meet you, Master Hechen.

629
00:35:50,040 --> 00:35:50,800
This way.

630
00:35:53,240 --> 00:35:54,320
Master. Mr. Kudo and

631
00:35:54,320 --> 00:35:55,760
his wife have arrived.

632
00:35:57,640 --> 00:35:59,570
Happy Mid-Autumn Festival, Tian.

633
00:35:59,720 --> 00:36:01,800
The Mid-Autumn Festival is
for family reunions.

634
00:36:01,800 --> 00:36:03,280
Why did you come here?

635
00:36:04,360 --> 00:36:05,920
I have no home in China.

636
00:36:06,120 --> 00:36:07,880
Your home is my home.

637
00:36:14,360 --> 00:36:15,640
How come your reading tutor

638
00:36:15,640 --> 00:36:18,280
is a beautiful lady now?

639
00:36:18,520 --> 00:36:20,480
This is Ms. Ding.

640
00:36:20,720 --> 00:36:21,840
This is Mr. Kudo.

641
00:36:22,320 --> 00:36:24,120
He was my classmate in Europe.

642
00:36:24,680 --> 00:36:25,760
And my best,

643
00:36:26,040 --> 00:36:27,440
my only Japanese friend.

644
00:36:27,840 --> 00:36:29,920
He's different
from other Japanese military officers.

645
00:36:29,920 --> 00:36:31,480
He's a true fan of China.

646
00:36:31,880 --> 00:36:32,880
Hello, Ms. Ding.

647
00:36:33,160 --> 00:36:35,240
I'm Kudo Shoichi.

648
00:36:35,640 --> 00:36:37,080
This is my wife, Setsuko.

649
00:36:39,080 --> 00:36:40,680
Happy Mid-Autumn Festival.

650
00:36:40,840 --> 00:36:43,000
This is a Mid-Autumn gift for you.

651
00:36:43,080 --> 00:36:45,440
Japanese moon cakes I made myself.

652
00:36:45,880 --> 00:36:48,240
In Japan we call them tsukimi dango.

653
00:36:48,840 --> 00:36:51,170
It's just a small token. Please accept it.

654
00:36:57,000 --> 00:36:58,240
You came to celebrate with me

655
00:36:58,240 --> 00:36:59,300
and brought gifts.

656
00:36:59,440 --> 00:37:02,400
Go. Tell Wanfu to bring some moon cakes.

657
00:37:03,240 --> 00:37:04,370
Master, one moment.

658
00:37:05,520 --> 00:37:06,200
Please sit.

659
00:37:06,920 --> 00:37:07,720
Tian,

660
00:37:08,480 --> 00:37:10,720
my wife has always wanted to see

661
00:37:11,000 --> 00:37:12,920
your airplane cockpit.

662
00:37:13,840 --> 00:37:16,720
Could you ask Ms. Ding

663
00:37:16,960 --> 00:37:18,560
to take her to see it?

664
00:37:23,560 --> 00:37:26,760
If you're not feeling well,

665
00:37:26,880 --> 00:37:28,480
you can also go home early.

666
00:37:29,520 --> 00:37:30,280
No problem.

667
00:37:33,960 --> 00:37:35,000
Madam, this way please.

668
00:37:35,000 --> 00:37:35,720
Thank you.

669
00:37:43,960 --> 00:37:44,600
Thank you.

670
00:37:50,040 --> 00:37:51,360
There's sand.

671
00:37:55,520 --> 00:37:56,440
May I?

672
00:38:17,320 --> 00:38:19,160
It still turns.

673
00:38:21,480 --> 00:38:24,160
Do you know what model this is?

674
00:38:26,120 --> 00:38:28,450
Mr. Tian told me
it was a... something Man.

675
00:38:29,200 --> 00:38:31,640
An improved model, I think.

676
00:38:32,200 --> 00:38:34,130
I don't really get it. I'm not sure.

677
00:38:34,960 --> 00:38:36,520
My husband told me

678
00:38:36,720 --> 00:38:38,560
about Mr. Tian flying this plane

679
00:38:38,640 --> 00:38:40,640
to the Alps.

680
00:38:41,040 --> 00:38:44,800
He said he and Mr. Tian
traveled the world,

681
00:38:44,920 --> 00:38:46,960
having many adventures.

682
00:38:47,160 --> 00:38:50,080
They're friends who have faced
life and death together.

683
00:38:50,080 --> 00:38:53,560
I didn't expect Mr. Tian to bring
the airplane cockpit home

684
00:38:53,600 --> 00:38:55,600
as a toy.

685
00:38:56,520 --> 00:38:59,320
Men really are boys who never grow up.

686
00:39:00,880 --> 00:39:03,520
The soap factory negotiations
went smoothly.

687
00:39:03,960 --> 00:39:07,420
Your position as honorary director
really made a difference.

688
00:39:07,560 --> 00:39:08,620
I have to thank you.

689
00:39:11,840 --> 00:39:13,040
It's nothing.

690
00:39:13,480 --> 00:39:16,760
Tian, I have good news for you.

691
00:39:18,320 --> 00:39:21,560
You know, I detest those arrogant

692
00:39:21,720 --> 00:39:24,040
and greedy guys from Army Headquarters.

693
00:39:24,400 --> 00:39:27,800
All those Chinese merchant factories

694
00:39:28,080 --> 00:39:29,480
managed by Army Headquarters
pass through their hands

695
00:39:29,480 --> 00:39:32,000
to end up in the hands
of Japanese conglomerates.

696
00:39:32,000 --> 00:39:34,480
They line their pockets in the process.

697
00:39:34,680 --> 00:39:37,040
Their economic control

698
00:39:37,400 --> 00:39:41,800
has satisfied the private interests
of a few Japanese magnates,

699
00:39:42,560 --> 00:39:45,400
but it has lost the support
of the Chinese people.

700
00:39:45,520 --> 00:39:46,650
Let's not talk about

701
00:39:47,840 --> 00:39:49,440
matters between countries.

702
00:39:50,360 --> 00:39:51,920
It sounds awkward.

703
00:39:52,480 --> 00:39:55,120
After all, I'm an economics professor.

704
00:39:55,800 --> 00:39:57,840
I've lived in Shanghai for so many years.

705
00:39:57,840 --> 00:40:01,320
I sincerely hope
Shanghai keeps prospering.

706
00:40:01,480 --> 00:40:05,320
So I just accepted a new position.

707
00:40:07,240 --> 00:40:08,100
What position?

708
00:40:10,640 --> 00:40:14,680
Senior advisor of
the Central China Development Company.

709
00:40:17,080 --> 00:40:20,920
What is
the Central China Development Company?

710
00:40:21,080 --> 00:40:22,560
It's a long story.

711
00:40:22,920 --> 00:40:26,560
The Central China Development Company
is being formed.

712
00:40:26,760 --> 00:40:30,080
Simply put, following Tokyo's directives,

713
00:40:30,400 --> 00:40:31,280
we'll use any means

714
00:40:31,280 --> 00:40:34,360
to make the economy
of the Central China region prosper.

715
00:40:34,360 --> 00:40:38,080
It's backed by
Japan's National Policy Company.

716
00:40:40,840 --> 00:40:41,840
National policy?

717
00:40:45,360 --> 00:40:48,020
I've only heard of
men's and women's restrooms.

718
00:40:49,760 --> 00:40:50,890
Tian, you still have

719
00:40:51,880 --> 00:40:55,000
that childish temperament.

720
00:40:56,720 --> 00:40:59,280
Kudo, didn't you always say

721
00:41:00,320 --> 00:41:01,780
you'd be a liberal scholar

722
00:41:02,080 --> 00:41:04,320
your whole life

723
00:41:04,880 --> 00:41:07,280
and never join the government or military?

724
00:41:07,520 --> 00:41:08,760
People change.

725
00:41:09,000 --> 00:41:10,760
Haven't you also changed
from an adventurer

726
00:41:10,760 --> 00:41:13,680
who loved to travel the world

727
00:41:13,800 --> 00:41:16,120
into a businessman?

728
00:41:23,720 --> 00:41:26,160
Kudo, two months ago,

729
00:41:26,280 --> 00:41:27,960
when I asked for your help,

730
00:41:28,680 --> 00:41:29,940
why didn't you tell me?

731
00:41:30,160 --> 00:41:34,280
To be honest, I hadn't decided yet.

732
00:41:40,480 --> 00:41:43,640
They were on an adventure
in the South American jungle.

733
00:41:43,840 --> 00:41:46,560
Kudo went to look for water and got lost.

734
00:41:46,880 --> 00:41:49,240
To rescue him,
Mr. Tian hung the supply pack on a tree,

735
00:41:49,240 --> 00:41:51,600
and it was stolen

736
00:41:51,960 --> 00:41:54,880
by monkeys.

737
00:42:00,240 --> 00:42:02,240
Then what about your nominal shares

738
00:42:02,440 --> 00:42:05,280
in the Pudong Soap Factory?

739
00:42:05,320 --> 00:42:06,320
What will happen to them?

740
00:42:06,320 --> 00:42:08,850
I'm convincing
the National Policy Company.

741
00:42:08,960 --> 00:42:11,360
I'll turn all the nominee shares

742
00:42:11,440 --> 00:42:13,360
into a real investment.

743
00:42:13,560 --> 00:42:14,360
This way,

744
00:42:14,800 --> 00:42:17,280
the military administration
of Tian's enterprises

745
00:42:17,280 --> 00:42:18,920
can be lifted immediately.

746
00:42:19,440 --> 00:42:21,400
Our factory will be a model

747
00:42:21,640 --> 00:42:23,640
for Japan-China cooperation.

748
00:42:23,960 --> 00:42:25,090
You have to trust me.

749
00:42:25,400 --> 00:42:27,400
I'm different from those soldiers.

750
00:42:27,560 --> 00:42:31,520
This is a civilized and equal
business partnership.

751
00:42:36,160 --> 00:42:38,080
Then the nature of this
changes completely.

752
00:42:38,080 --> 00:42:40,560
Tian, change brings fluidity.

753
00:42:40,680 --> 00:42:42,080
Change brings fluidity.

754
00:42:42,920 --> 00:42:44,580
Rigidity brings stagnation.

755
00:42:44,960 --> 00:42:47,560
Change brings prosperity.
Rigidity brings decline.

756
00:42:47,560 --> 00:42:50,360
Change brings life,
while rigidity brings death.

757
00:42:50,880 --> 00:42:51,880
Is that what you mean?

758
00:42:51,880 --> 00:42:52,680
No.

759
00:42:52,960 --> 00:42:55,040
Change brings fluidity,
fluidity brings success,

760
00:42:55,040 --> 00:42:56,900
and success brings fulfillment.

761
00:42:59,920 --> 00:43:02,120
So I can't even have a different opinion,

762
00:43:02,120 --> 00:43:04,120
right?
